			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Been a while since I stopped by, I've been very busy playing City of Heroes as it happens.  Fun game by the way, I recommend it.  But my point in addressng CoH and this thread is as follows:
<br />

<br />
I tend to look at the classes in terms of primary/secondary abilities,  where a class has perhaps one of each, or sacrifices a primary for an additional secondary.  Whether I am right or wrong, or just plain "out there", I see the classes as such:
<br />

<br />
Beastlord: Pet (Primary), Melee (Secondary), Healer/Buffer (Tertiary)
<br />
Magician: Pet (Primary), Spells, DD (Secondary), Summons/CoH (Tertiary)
<br />
Necromancer: Pet (Primary), Spells, DoT (Secondary), Spells, Utility (Tertiary)
<br />

<br />
Comparitively:
<br />
Shaman: Player Buff/Mob Debuff (Primary), Pet (Secondary), Healer (Tertiary)
<br />
Cleric: Healer (Primary), Player Buffing (Secondary), Rezzing (Tertiary)
<br />
Druid: Healer (Secondary), Spells, DD (Secondary), Spells, Utility (Tertiary)
<br />

<br />
Fairly imperfect I admit, but my point is that "mages are supposed to have the best pets and beastlords are just a hybrid" isn't really fair, nor is it accurate really.  A while ago (around Luclin if I recall) the decision was made to "de-gimp" hybrids and make them their own unique classes with an assortment of abilities that made them the equal of another class that wasn't a hybrid. So "hybrid" besically means they mix magic & non-magical means of doing stuff instead of having their stuff be all one or the other.
<br />

<br />
In the case of the beasties, they like magicians are very dependant on their pets.  Without a lot of melee AA and very good gear, an equivilent monk is going to be too busy mocking them to remember to feign off aggro <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="wink" border="0" />  Combined with their pets they are quite respectable of course, but then again magician + nukes is also pretty respectable DPS.  Ultimately, outside of both classes being "pet primary" they play very differantly and have differant concerns and issues.  So I have to confess I really don't get this whole class-rivalry that's going on.<br />_________________<br />EQ1: Zarros (65 cleric), Saryrn Server
<br />
EQ1: Zanros (65 beastlord), Saryrn Server
<br />
CoH: Tachyon Trinity (23 blaster), Virtue</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
